{"word":"κούριμος","slug":"κούριμος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κούριμος</b></el> <el>(κούριμος, η, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κουρά'><el>κουρά</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>of, for cutting hair</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <i>shorn off</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>shorn</i>, <el>κρᾶτα</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}